node.text:
Are you ready to dance again? Here, famed dancers Melissa Verdecia, Calvin Royal III, Xin Ying, Misty Copeland, Savion Glover, Stella Abrera, Vinson Fraley, Lloyd Knight, Courtney Celeste Spears, Tatiana Desardouin, and Tiler Peck showcase each of their individual style and expression of dance.

Featuring: @mmelifern @calvinroyaliii @xin_ying_dance @mistyonpointe the_savionglover @stellaabreradetsky @heyvinson @lloydknight @bahamaballerina @tatianadesardouin @tilerpeck

Director + Director of Photography: @mr_dume
Stylist: @samiranasr
Producers: @kriceee @imurillo
Assistant Camera: @forthexperience
Editor: @mr_dume
Colorist: @ericaharperdillman
Motion Designer: @annaaaiello
Entertainment Director: @angcutt

node.title: Misty Copeland, Savion Glover & More World-Class Dancers Are Back on Stage

node.text:
Our August cover star @GigiHadid embarks on her dream cake-baking internship under #CakeBoss's own @BuddyValastro, the prolific baker of cakes best known for his impressive larger-than-life cake designs. Here, Gigi talks cooking and baking with her family on the farm, everything bagel pregnancy cravings, and favorite ‘Cake Boss’ moments.

Director: @isabel.c.montes
Producer: @kriceee
Editor + Colorist: @ericaharperdillman
Director of Photography: @mr_dume
Camera: @22jezu
Audio: @dave_scaringe_sound
Stylist: @mimicuttrell
Makeup Artist: @cgonzalezbeauty
Hair Stylist: @jennifer_yepez
Special thanks to @carlosbakery

node.title: Gigi Hadid Shows Off Her Cake Decorating Skills With Cake Boss

node.text: Michaela Jaé AKA @MjRodriguez7 knows the importance of sharing her story, whether it’s on-screen, starring as Blanca in @PoseonFX or in her everyday life. In this episode of #GoToBedWithMe, she shares with us her full nighttime skincare routine, her beauty icon, and how she keeps her skin hydrated.

node.title: ‘Pose’ Star Mj Rodriguez’s Nighttime Skincare Routine

node.text: @PattieGonia is a trailblazing drag queen, intersectional environmentalist, and photographer whose mission is to bring drag, diversity, and community to the great outdoors. node.text:
Happy 40th birthday #MeghanMarkle! Today, the Duchess of Sussex has launched a new charitable initiative to support women around the world. As part of the Archewell Foundation’s ongoing call for Compassion in Action, the new 40x40 initiative encourages people to contribute 40 minutes of mentorship or community service to help women affected by the pandemic reenter the workforce. “With my 40th lap around the sun in mind, it made me wonder: what would happen if we all committed 40 minutes to helping someone else or to mentoring someone in need?” the duchess wrote. “And then what would happen if we asked our friends to do the same?” Meghan has enlisted the help of 40 activists, athletes, artists, and world leaders, including the likes of Adele, Amanda Gorman, Gloria Steinem, Stella McCartney, and more. Tap the link in bio to learn more.

Photo Credit: Archewell

“Performing is very natural for me. I think that confuses some people, and it has them thinking that I’m performing all the time,” says comedian and @InsecureHBO actor @AmandaSeales for our August issue. “It’s not that. It just takes nothing for me to perform. I don’t have to flip a switch to talk to folks on a stage. I know Beyoncé will talk about how she has Sasha Fierce. I just have louder Amanda.” At the link in bio, she talks to @kaitlyn_greenidge_author about stepping up to the stand-up mic for the first time in a year, and why, for her, creativity comes from living in the moment.

node.text: Fall is still weeks away, but street style is already serving inspiration for the new season. node.text: This past weekend, Missouri Congresswoman @CoriBush camped overnight outside the Capitol building to protest the end of the eviction moratorium, which was installed last year to help Americans facing unemployment during the pandemic. Now that the Democrat-controlled House of Representatives adjourned for its summer break without extending the eviction freeze, millions of Americans are left vulnerable to eviction and homelessness. “I remember what it was like for us to live out of my car. I think about how society wanted me to believe that being unhoused was my fault,” wrote Representative Bush in a letter to her colleagues. “We have a deeply rooted misconception in our country that unhoused people have done something to deserve their conditions–when the reality is that unhoused people are living the consequences of our government’s failure to secure the basic necessities people need to survive.” Read more at the link in bio.
